# Code Knowledge Graph

This project is indexed by the **cursor-project-manager** MCP server. A structured
graph lives at `.cursor/knowledge_graph.json` mapping every file, class, function,
import, and reverse-dependency with exact line ranges.

## Use the graph BEFORE scanning source files

1. To find a class/function/enum, call the `query_symbol` tool — it returns the
   exact `file` and `lines` `[start, end]`. Then read only those lines.
2. Before changing a file, call `query_file` and check `importedBy` to find every
   file affected by the change.
3. Never blindly scan or read whole files when the graph can point you to the
   exact location.
4. After completing a set of code changes, call `update_knowledge_graph` to keep
   the graph current (it only re-parses changed files via git).

## Available MCP tools

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `load_project` | Start work on a project; auto-generates the graph |
| `get_project_info` | Tech stack, source dir, git status, graph status |
| `generate_knowledge_graph` | Full re-scan of all Python source |
| `update_knowledge_graph` | Incremental update for changed files |
| `query_symbol` | Find a symbol's file + line range |
| `query_file` | A file's symbols, imports, and `importedBy` |
| `list_recent_projects` | Recently loaded projects |

## Graph schema (key sections)

- `meta`: language, sourceDir, totalFiles, totalSymbols, generatedAt
- `files.<path>`: `description`, `lines`, `symbols`, `imports`, `importedBy`
- `symbols.<Name>`: `kind`, `file`, `lines [start,end]`, `extends`, `members`
- `routes`: detected FastAPI/Flask endpoints → `file:function`

If the graph seems stale, run `update_knowledge_graph`; for a full rebuild run
`generate_knowledge_graph`.
